cs.NI, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.AI, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on resource allocation in cellular networks.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a machine learning approach for resource allocation.
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses the trade-off between spectral efficiency and overhead costs.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper proposes a machine learning approach for resource allocation.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is less likely but still relevant as the paper discusses the design of a CRAN system and its resource allocation.
